step panel a rewarding experience education and society theme house step panel a rewarding experience submitted by jchu1225 on thu 11 04 2010 12 16 why become a teacher because every day is an adventure every morning when i wake up i look forward to my job why enroll in the stanford teacher education program step step cultivates teacher leaders graduates of step are sought after by schools in the bay area and other parts of california these are just some of the insights shared at the education and society theme east house on november 2 2010 in our discussion with step students and alumni joining us that night to share their stories and advice were current step students katie peterson english secondary ed and sarah macway biology secondary ed and step alumni jeff camarillo vice principal east palo alto academy and lauri anderson fiesta gardens elementary polly diffenbaugh step 97 was on hand to explain step's structure and options and to provide guidance on the application process the roughly 18 students in attendance represented a wide variety of years and majors everyone left believing in jeff camarillo's words there is no more noble profession than being a teacher login to post comments home welcome we are the education and society theme east house directions here we seek to establish the salience of education and the relationship between education and society on stanford campus through outreach to undergraduates and residential based programming please contact us with any comments or suggestions new forum topics photographs for waiting for superman more user login username password request new password education and society theme house calendar of events programs at east living at east bulletin board about us contact us visit the education theme house at 544 governor's avenue between lagunita and frosoco drupal theme designed by blamcast
